    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><strong>Deep Magic: </strong>winter</em><br>This spell invokes the deepest part of night on the winter solstice. You target a 40-foot-radius, 60-foot-high cylinder centered on a point within range, which is plunged into darkness and unbearable cold. Each creature in the area when you cast the spell and at the start of its turn must make a successful Constitution saving throw or take 1d6 cold damage and gain one level of @Compendium[dnd5e.rules.apBZudO4UA1wj7aC]{exhaustion}. Creatures immune to cold damage are also immune to the exhaustion effect, as are creatures wearing cold weather gear or otherwise adapted for a cold environment.<br>As a bonus action, you can move the center of the effect 20 feet.",
